<p><strong>The Wonderful Name of Jesus by E.W. Kenyon</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary:</strong></p>
<p>"The Wonderful Name of Jesus" by E.W. Kenyon is an insightful exploration of the power and significance of the name of Jesus. Kenyon uncovers its biblical basis, its practical application in daily life, and its implications for victory over sin and sickness.</p>
<p><strong>Q1: What is the biblical basis for the power of Jesus' name?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Kenyon cites numerous Bible passages that attribute great authority and power to the name of Jesus. He points to verses such as Philippians 2:9-11, which declares that at the name of Jesus "every knee should bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth."</p>
<p><strong>Q2: How can the name of Jesus be used in practical life?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Kenyon emphasizes the transformative power of speaking and invoking the name of Jesus. He encourages readers to use it when facing challenges, seeking healing, or interceding for others. By declaring the name of Jesus, believers can access its power and experience its transformative effects.</p>
<p><strong>Q3: What are the implications of the name of Jesus for victory over sin and sickness?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Kenyon asserts that the name of Jesus carries power over both sin and sickness. Through faith in the name, believers can break free from the bondage of sin and receive divine healing. The name of Jesus empowers them to overcome obstacles and live a life of victory.</p>
<p><strong>Q4: How can we access the power of Jesus' name?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Kenyon explains that to experience the full power of Jesus' name, believers must have a personal relationship with Him. By accepting Jesus as their Savior and Lord, they are connected to the source of its power. Additionally, he encourages readers to meditate on the name of Jesus and declare its significance in their lives.</p>
<p><strong>Q5: What are the benefits of knowing and using the name of Jesus?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Kenyon asserts that the name of Jesus brings blessings, protection, joy, and victory. By knowing and using His name, believers can experience a closer relationship with Him, overcome challenges, and live a life filled with purpose and meaning.</p>